Rune magic is an ancient practice of [[arcane magic]] practiced by the titans of [[Xen'drik]] during the [[Age of Giants]]. Runes of power are ancient sigils that embody the fundamental magic of creation. Each rune holds latent power, like the glyphs inscribed in modern [[magic circle]]s of protection, [[teleportation circle]]s, and magical traps like the [[glyph of warding]]. It is believed that the magic of these runes allowed the titans of the past age to grow in stature far beyond the towering heights of modern [[giant]]s.

The ancient giants treated these runes as a sacred secret and rarely wrote them, but even writing them is not sufficient to channel their power. Most modern true [[giant]]s are able to shape and invoke runes, as the ancient magic still runs through their blood. Non-giants can learn this power, but typically only after tutelage by a giant sage, or if they have some innate connection to the magic of the ancient titans. These modern runewielders include [[rune knight]]s and [[rune shaper|Rune Shaper]]s.

