!! Items Which Utilize Rune Magic

Some [[magic item]]s have been imbued with one or more runes of power. These items can grant new powers and abilities to those who [[attune|attunement]] to them, but typically they unlock additional powers if the wielder knows how to "invoke" the item's rune. Learning how to invoke runes is less challenging than learning how to inscribe them, but still requires training. A character might gain the ability to invoke runes after completing a "long-term project" during <<navAndScrollToHeader "Missions and Downtime" "downtime">> in which they study or meditate on the secrets of channeling rune magic.

If a magic item was created to be used by [[giant]]s, it might be too oversized to use properly by a human-sized creature. You might decide that the giants crafted magic items that can resize to comfortably suit their users during the [[attunement]] process. Alternatively, you can say that a giant-sized ring can be worn as a bracelet, a bracelet could serve as a headband, and so on. In addition, magical techniques might exist that allow skilled artisans to reshape and resize magic items with a few days of work.

